   The Pediatric Oncology Branch of the National Cancer Institute is part
   of the National Institutes of Health (NIH), the world's largest medical
   research institution, which is operated by the federal government.
   Patients who participate in clinical protocols are treated at the
   Clinical Center located on the NIH campus in Bethesda, Maryland. This
   Home Page provides patients, families and physicians with an overview
   of the type of treatments available for children with cancer, and of
   the research conducted by investigators at the Pediatric Oncology
   Branch.
   Please read the disclaimer regarding material presented on the
   Pediatric Oncology Branch of the NCI Home Page.
   To learn more about the Pediatric Oncology Branch, explore the
   following areas:

     * Clinical Trial Overview
     * Pediatric Oncology Branch Protocols
     * Pediatric Oncology Branch Research
     * Pediatric Oncology Branch Staff Directory
     * Finding a Protocol
     * Recent Publications
     * Frequently Asked Questions
     * A Visit to the Pediatric Oncology Branch
     * Referring a Patient
     * The Children's Inn at NIH
     * Fellowship Training Program
     * Other Sites of Interest

   Again, thanks for visiting the Pediatric Oncology Branch's web site. We
   hope that you find this information useful and accessible

